            <h2>{{t "I. Introduction & Agreement" key="terms_section_i_heading"}}</h2>

            <h3>{{t "1. Welcome to LingoLinq" key="terms_welcome_heading"}}</h3>
            <p>{{t "Welcome to LingoLinq. These Terms of Service (\"Terms\") govern your access to and use of the LingoLinq website (www.lingolinq.com) and all associated products and services (collectively, the \"Service\"). By accessing or using the Service, you agree to be bound by these Terms." key="terms_intro"}}</p>

            <h3>{{t "2. Notice of Updates" key="terms_notice_updates_heading"}}</h3>
            <p>{{t "LingoLinq will provide 30 days' advance notice for modifications to this Agreement impacting billing, data privacy, or core usage rights. We will deliver this notice via:" key="terms_notice_updates_intro"}}</p>
            <ul>
              <li>{{t "an announcement on the LingoLinq Dashboard; and" key="terms_notice_updates_1"}}</li>
              <li>{{t "a message to the primary email address associated with your account." key="terms_notice_updates_2"}}</li>
            </ul>
            <p>{{t "Following the posting of a material change to this Agreement, the 30-day notice period begins. During this window, you will be prompted to review and accept the updated terms via a notification overlay each time you log in to the Site or Product. You may continue to use LingoLinq under your existing terms during this 30-day window." key="terms_notice_updates_period"}}</p>
            <p><strong>{{t "Mandatory Acceptance for Continued Use" key="terms_mandatory_acceptance_heading"}}</strong> — {{t "To maintain your account after the 30-day notice period ends, you must affirmatively click \"I Accept.\" If you have not provided express electronic consent by the end of the notice period, your access to the Site and Product will be automatically discontinued." key="terms_mandatory_acceptance"}}</p>
            <p><strong>{{t "Account Restoration & Data Export" key="terms_account_restoration_heading"}}</strong> — {{t "If your access is closed due to non-acceptance, you may restore it at any time by logging in and accepting the updated Agreement. If you choose not to accept the new terms, you may use the Account Settings tool during the 30-day notice period to export your data and permanently close your account." key="terms_account_restoration"}}</p>

            <h3>{{t "3. Electronic Contracting" key="terms_electronic_contracting_heading"}}</h3>
            <p>{{t "By clicking \"Accept\", \"Create Account\", or \"Submit Payment\", you acknowledge that you have read, understood, and agree to be bound by these Terms, and the Privacy Policy." key="terms_electronic_contracting"}}</p>

            <h2>{{t "II. Accounts & Compliance" key="terms_section_ii_heading"}}</h2>

            <h3>{{t "1. Account Responsibilities" key="terms_account_heading"}}</h3>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>{{t "Account Creation:" key="terms_account_creation_heading"}}</strong> {{t "You must provide accurate information when creating an account. Account Administrators (e.g., parents, therapists, school districts) are responsible for safeguarding their passwords and for all activities that occur under their account, including the actions of the \"Communicators\" (the end-users) they manage." key="terms_account_creation"}}</li>
              <li><strong>{{t "Authorized Use:" key="terms_authorized_use_heading"}}</strong> {{t "You agree to use the Service only for its intended purpose as an Augmentative and Alternative Communication (AAC) tool and educational support system." key="terms_authorized_use"}}</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>{{t "2. Data Privacy and Regulatory Compliance" key="terms_data_privacy_heading"}}</h3>
            <p>{{t "LingoLinq is committed to protecting the sensitive data of our users, particularly children and individuals utilizing our app for clinical or educational support." key="terms_data_privacy_intro"}}</p>
            <p><strong>{{t "Privacy Policy Integration:" key="terms_privacy_policy_heading"}}</strong> {{t "Your access to and use of the Service is subject to the LingoLinq Privacy Policy, which details how we collect, store, and encrypt your data. By using LingoLinq, you acknowledge and consent to our data practices as outlined in the Privacy Policy." key="terms_privacy_policy"}}</p>
            <p><strong>{{t "COPPA (Children's Privacy & Consent):" key="terms_coppa_heading"}}</strong> {{t "LingoLinq accounts must be created and managed by an adult Account Administrator (e.g., a parent, therapist, or school official). If the \"Communicator\" (the end-user) is a child under the age of 13, the Account Administrator represents and warrants that they are the parent or legal guardian, or that they have obtained verifiable parental consent, for the child to use the Product and for LingoLinq to process their data in accordance with the Children's Online Privacy Protection Act (COPPA)." key="terms_coppa"}}</p>
            <p><strong>{{t "HIPAA (Healthcare Providers & Clinics):" key="terms_hipaa_heading"}}</strong> {{t "LingoLinq provides a secure platform, but we are not inherently a \"Covered Entity\" under the Health Insurance Portability and Accountability Act (HIPAA). If you are a healthcare provider, clinic, or other Covered Entity intending to use LingoLinq to store or transmit Protected Health Information (PHI), you must execute a formal Business Associate Agreement (BAA) with LingoLinq prior to uploading any PHI into the Service." key="terms_hipaa"}}</p>
            <p><strong>{{t "FERPA (Schools & Educational Institutions):" key="terms_ferpa_heading"}}</strong> {{t "When LingoLinq is contracted by a school district or educational agency to provide AAC services for students, LingoLinq acts as a \"School Official\" with a legitimate educational interest. We strictly comply with the Family Educational Rights and Privacy Act (FERPA) by maintaining the confidentiality and security of all student education records and custom vocabulary boards, and we will never use student data for targeted advertising or unauthorized commercial purposes." key="terms_ferpa"}}</p>

            <h2>{{t "III. Acceptable Use & Content" key="terms_section_iii_heading"}}</h2>

            <h3>{{t "1. Acceptable Use Policy" key="terms_acceptable_use_heading"}}</h3>
            <p>{{t "You agree not to:" key="terms_acceptable_use_intro"}}</p>
            <ul>
              <li>{{t "Use the Service for any illegal or unauthorized purpose." key="terms_acceptable_use_1"}}</li>
              <li>{{t "Upload viruses, malicious code, or attempt to breach our security systems." key="terms_acceptable_use_2"}}</li>
              <li>{{t "Infringe upon the intellectual property rights of others when uploading custom images or audio." key="terms_acceptable_use_3"}}</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>{{t "2. User-Generated Content" key="terms_ugc_heading"}}</h3>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>{{t "Ownership:" key="terms_ugc_ownership_heading"}}</strong> {{t "You retain all ownership rights to the vocabulary boards, images, audio, and customized buttons (\"User Content\") you create or upload." key="terms_ugc_ownership"}}</li>
              <li><strong>{{t "License to LingoLinq:" key="terms_ugc_license_heading"}}</strong> {{t "By uploading User Content, you grant LingoLinq a secure, non-exclusive, worldwide license to host, store, and back up this content solely for the purpose of providing the Service to you and your authorized supervisors." key="terms_ugc_license"}}</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>{{t "3. Feedback License" key="terms_feedback_heading"}}</h3>
            <p>{{t "While you have no obligation to provide suggestions or feedback, if you do provide feedback relating to the Service, you grant LingoLinq LLC a perpetual, irrevocable, royalty-free license to use and commercialize such feedback to improve the Product or for any other purpose." key="terms_feedback"}}</p>

            <h2>{{t "IV. Intellectual Property & Software" key="terms_section_iv_heading"}}</h2>

            <h3>{{t "1. Ownership, Open Source, and Intellectual Property" key="terms_ip_heading"}}</h3>
            <p><strong>{{t "Source-Available Codebase:" key="terms_ip_source_heading"}}</strong> {{t "LingoLinq believes in community-driven accessibility. The underlying source code for the LingoLinq platform is made publicly available under the GNU AGPLv3. Any downloading, modification, or distribution of the source code itself is governed strictly by the terms of that separate license agreement, which can be found in our public repository." key="terms_ip_source"}}</p>
            <p><strong>{{t "Anti-Commercialization Restriction:" key="terms_ip_anti_commercial_heading"}}</strong> {{t "While our code is accessible to the public for educational, personal, and developmental use, you may not commercialize the Product. Except as explicitly permitted by our repository license, you may not copy, modify, re-package, white-label, or distribute the LingoLinq software, app, or any derivative works for commercial gain, subscription fees, or monetary compensation without a separate, explicit commercial agreement from LingoLinq." key="terms_ip_anti_commercial"}}</p>
            <p><strong>{{t "LingoLinq's Hosted Service and Trademarks:" key="terms_ip_trademarks_heading"}}</strong> {{t "Your access to the official, hosted LingoLinq app and website is licensed, not sold. While the underlying code may be accessible, LingoLinq retains all exclusive ownership of its brand identity, including its name, trademarks, service marks, logos, and the specific database infrastructure hosting the Product. You may not use LingoLinq's branding to endorse or promote your own modified versions of the software." key="terms_ip_trademarks"}}</p>
            <p><strong>{{t "Your Personal Content:" key="terms_ip_personal_heading"}}</strong> {{t "LingoLinq does not claim ownership over your personal User-Generated Content. Any custom photos, voice recordings, or individualized data you upload into the Product remain entirely your property, and are not subject to any public or open-source licensing." key="terms_ip_personal"}}</p>

            <h3>{{t "2. Limited License & Restrictions" key="terms_limited_license_heading"}}</h3>
            <p><strong>{{t "Grant of License:" key="terms_license_grant_heading"}}</strong> {{t "Subject to your compliance with this Agreement, LingoLinq grants you a personal, non-exclusive, non-transferable, and revocable license to access and use the Site and Product on your personal devices. This license is for your own internal, non-commercial use only." key="terms_license_grant"}}</p>
            <p><strong>{{t "Prohibited Actions:" key="terms_prohibited_heading"}}</strong> {{t "Except as expressly permitted by our open-source repository license (e.g., AGPLv3) or by LingoLinq in writing, you agree not to:" key="terms_prohibited_intro"}}</p>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>{{t "Commercialize" key="terms_prohibited_commercial_label"}}</strong> — {{t "Sell, resell, white-label, or commercially exploit the hosted Service or any modified versions of the software." key="terms_prohibited_commercial"}}</li>
              <li><strong>{{t "Bypass Security" key="terms_prohibited_security_label"}}</strong> — {{t "Attempt to hack, bypass, or circumvent the security, billing, or access controls of the official, hosted LingoLinq platform." key="terms_prohibited_security"}}</li>
              <li><strong>{{t "Misappropriate Branding" key="terms_prohibited_branding_label"}}</strong> — {{t "Copy or use LingoLinq's proprietary trademarks, logos, or unique visual designs to create a confusingly similar or rival product." key="terms_prohibited_branding"}}</li>
              <li><strong>{{t "Disrupt the Service" key="terms_prohibited_disrupt_label"}}</strong> — {{t "Use automated scripts, scrapers, or excessive requests that burden our hosted servers or disrupt the experience for other users." key="terms_prohibited_disrupt"}}</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>{{t "V. Billing & Subscriptions" key="terms_section_v_heading"}}</h2>

            <h3>{{t "1. Payment, Auto-Renewal, and Cancellation" key="terms_billing_heading"}}</h3>
            <p><strong>{{t "Subscription and Auto-Renewal:" key="terms_billing_auto_renewal_heading"}}</strong> {{t "LingoLinq offers monthly and annual subscriptions. By subscribing, you authorize us to automatically charge your payment method on file on a recurring basis. All subscriptions automatically renew for the same term length unless canceled or modified prior to the renewal date. Subscriptions will auto-renew at the standard subscription price in effect at the moment of renewal. If you registered under a promotional or discounted rate, your subscription will automatically renew at the end of the promotional term at the full, standard subscription price in effect at that time." key="terms_billing_auto_renewal"}}</p>
            <p><strong>{{t "Cancellation and Self-Service:" key="terms_billing_cancellation_heading"}}</strong> {{t "You may cancel or modify your subscription at any time through your Account Settings dashboard. Modifications can include switching your billing term or applying a new, valid promotional offer to your upcoming renewal. To avoid being charged for the next billing cycle—including the automatic conversion of a promotional subscription to a full-priced subscription—you must cancel or finalize your modifications before your current term expires. If you cancel, you will retain full access to the Product until the end of your currently paid billing period, and you will not be billed again." key="terms_billing_cancellation"}}</p>
            <p><strong>{{t "No Refunds:" key="terms_billing_refunds_heading"}}</strong> {{t "All fees are non-refundable. LingoLinq does not provide refunds or credits for partial months of service, unused months, downgraded accounts, or early cancellation of an annual term." key="terms_billing_refunds"}}</p>
            <p><strong>{{t "Failed Payments:" key="terms_billing_failed_heading"}}</strong> {{t "If your payment method fails, LingoLinq will attempt to notify you. If payment is not updated and successfully processed, your access to the Product will be automatically suspended until the account is brought current." key="terms_billing_failed"}}</p>
            <p><strong>{{t "Price Changes & Price Lock:" key="terms_billing_price_heading"}}</strong> {{t "We may change our subscription pricing from time to time, but we will never change your price in the middle of a paid term. Any price changes will only apply to your next renewal period (e.g., your next month for monthly plans, or your next year for annual plans). We will provide you with at least 30 days' advance notice via the email address on your account before any price increase takes effect, giving you the opportunity to cancel or modify your subscription before the new rate is charged." key="terms_billing_price"}}</p>
            <p><strong>{{t "Taxes:" key="terms_billing_taxes_heading"}}</strong> {{t "All listed fees are exclusive of applicable taxes or duties. You are solely responsible for paying any taxes associated with your purchase based on your billing jurisdiction." key="terms_billing_taxes"}}</p>

            <h2>{{t "VI. Disclaimers & Service Availability" key="terms_section_vi_heading"}}</h2>

            <h3>{{t "1. Medical Disclaimer & Emergency Use" key="terms_medical_heading"}}</h3>
            <p>{{t "LingoLinq provides an Augmentative and Alternative Communication (AAC) software tool designed to assist with expressive communication. LingoLinq is a technology provider, not a healthcare provider. We do not provide medical, therapeutic, or diagnostic advice, nor does the use of our Product create a provider-patient relationship." key="terms_medical_intro"}}</p>
            <p>{{t "While LingoLinq may be used in clinical or educational settings alongside Speech-Language Pathologists (SLPs), educators, or medical professionals, the Product is not a substitute for professional clinical judgment, diagnosis, or treatment. Always consult qualified healthcare or educational professionals regarding specific communication or medical needs." key="terms_medical_clinical"}}</p>
            <p>{{t "Do not rely on LingoLinq in a life-threatening or medical emergency. The Product is software operating on consumer devices and is subject to battery depletion, software crashes, and internet outages. If you, or a user are experiencing a medical emergency, utilize standard emergency services immediately. LingoLinq is not liable for any delays in medical treatment caused by technical failures or miscommunications arising from the use of the Product." key="terms_medical_emergency"}}</p>
            <p>{{t "LingoLinq does not monitor, verify, or endorse the medical accuracy of any custom vocabulary, phrases, or communications generated by users, parents, or therapists within the Product." key="terms_medical_accuracy"}}</p>

            <h3>{{t "2. Availability and Service Changes" key="terms_availability_heading"}}</h3>
            <p><strong>{{t "Service Availability:" key="terms_availability_service_heading"}}</strong> {{t "While LingoLinq aims to provide a consistent user experience, the Site and Product are provided on an \"as-available\" basis. Access may be interrupted by scheduled maintenance, emergency repairs, or failures of third-party telecommunications and equipment. LingoLinq is not responsible for any losses or data corruption resulting from these interruptions." key="terms_availability_service"}}</p>
            <p><strong>{{t "Right to Modify:" key="terms_availability_modify_heading"}}</strong> {{t "LingoLinq is an evolving product. We reserve the right to add, modify, or remove features and functionality at any time without prior notice." key="terms_availability_modify"}}</p>
            <p><strong>{{t "No Liability for Service Changes:" key="terms_availability_liability_heading"}}</strong> {{t "You agree that LingoLinq will not be liable to you or any third party for any modification, price change, suspension, or discontinuance of the Service. Your sole remedy for dissatisfaction with any service changes is to stop using the Product." key="terms_availability_liability"}}</p>

            <h3>{{t "3. Disclaimer of Warranties" key="terms_warranties_heading"}}</h3>
            <p><strong>{{t "PROVIDED \"AS-IS\":" key="terms_warranties_as_is_heading"}}</strong> {{t "TO THE MAXIMUM EXTENT PERMITTED BY LAW, THE SITE, PRODUCT, AND CONTENT ARE PROVIDED ON AN \"AS IS\" AND \"AS AVAILABLE\" BASIS. YOUR USE OF LINGOLINQ IS AT YOUR SOLE RISK." key="terms_warranties_as_is"}}</p>
            <p><strong>{{t "NO IMPLIED WARRANTIES:" key="terms_warranties_implied_heading"}}</strong> {{t "LINGOLINQ EXPRESSLY DISCLAIMS ALL WARRANTIES OF ANY KIND, WHETHER EXPRESS, IMPLIED, OR STATUTORY. THIS INCLUDES, BUT IS NOT LIMITED TO, THE IMPLIED WARRANTIES OF MERCHANTABILITY, FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE, TITLE, AND NON-INFRINGEMENT." key="terms_warranties_implied"}}</p>
            <p><strong>{{t "NO GUARANTEE OF TECHNICAL PERFECTION:" key="terms_warranties_technical_heading"}}</strong> {{t "WE DO NOT WARRANT THAT THE PRODUCT WILL BE ERROR-FREE, UNINTERRUPTED, SECURE, OR FREE OF VIRUSES OR OTHER HARMFUL COMPONENTS. WE DO NOT GUARANTEE THAT ANY SPECIFIC DEFECTS WILL BE CORRECTED." key="terms_warranties_technical"}}</p>
            <p><strong>{{t "NO GUARANTEE OF EDUCATIONAL RESULTS:" key="terms_warranties_educational_heading"}}</strong> {{t "LINGOLINQ IS A LEARNING TOOL, BUT WE DO NOT GUARANTEE ANY SPECIFIC LANGUAGE PROFICIENCY, TEST SCORES, OR OTHER MEASURABLE RESULTS FROM YOUR USE OF THE PRODUCT. YOUR SUCCESS DEPENDS ENTIRELY ON YOUR OWN EFFORT AND APPLICATION." key="terms_warranties_educational"}}</p>

            <h2>{{t "VII. Legal Defenses & Liability" key="terms_section_vii_heading"}}</h2>

