            <p><strong>{{t "Public Institution Exception:" key="terms_indemnification_public_heading"}}</strong> {{t "If you are a public school, government agency, or other public entity utilizing LingoLinq for educational or clinical purposes, this indemnification section will not apply to you to the extent that it is prohibited by your jurisdiction's laws regarding sovereign immunity or public indemnification." key="terms_indemnification_public"}}</p>
            <p><strong>{{t "Control of Defense:" key="terms_indemnification_control_heading"}}</strong> {{t "If LingoLinq is sued due to your actions, we reserve the right to assume the exclusive legal defense and control of the matter at our own expense. In such cases, you agree to fully cooperate with our legal team in defending the claim." key="terms_indemnification_control"}}</p>
            <p><strong>{{t "Survival:" key="terms_indemnification_survival_heading"}}</strong> {{t "This obligation to protect LingoLinq will survive even after you delete your account or stop using the Product." key="terms_indemnification_survival"}}</p>

            <h3>{{t "3. Force Majeure" key="terms_force_majeure_heading"}}</h3>
            <p>{{t "LingoLinq shall not be liable for any failure or delay in performance under these Terms due to circumstances beyond our reasonable control, including but not limited to acts of God, natural disasters, cyber warfare, systemic internet outages, or government actions." key="terms_force_majeure"}}</p>

            <h3>{{t "4. Export Control & U.S. Compliance" key="terms_export_heading"}}</h3>
            <p>{{t "You represent and warrant that:" key="terms_export_intro"}}</p>
            <ul>
              <li>{{t "you are not located in a country subject to a U.S. Government embargo or designated as a \"terrorist supporting\" country; and" key="terms_export_1"}}</li>
              <li>{{t "you are not listed on any U.S. Government list of prohibited or restricted parties." key="terms_export_2"}}</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>{{t "VIII. Dispute Resolution & Termination" key="terms_section_viii_heading"}}</h2>

            <h3>{{t "1. Governing Law and Dispute Resolution" key="terms_dispute_heading"}}</h3>
            <p><strong>{{t "Choice of Law and Venue:" key="terms_dispute_venue_heading"}}</strong> {{t "This Agreement, and any dispute arising from it, will be governed by the laws of the State of Utah, without regard to its conflict of law principles. Any legal suit or proceeding must be brought exclusively in the state courts located in Weber County, Utah, or the federal courts located in Salt Lake City, Utah. By using LingoLinq, you consent to the personal jurisdiction and venue of these courts." key="terms_dispute_venue"}}</p>
            <p><strong>{{t "JURY TRIAL AND CLASS ACTION WAIVER:" key="terms_dispute_waiver_heading"}}</strong> {{t "YOU AND LINGOLINQ MUTUALLY WAIVE ANY RIGHT TO A TRIAL BY JURY. FURTHERMORE, ANY LEGAL PROCEEDINGS WILL BE CONDUCTED ONLY ON AN INDIVIDUAL BASIS AND NOT IN A CLASS, CONSOLIDATED, OR REPRESENTATIVE ACTION. YOU WAIVE ANY RIGHT TO BRING A CLAIM AS A PLAINTIFF OR CLASS MEMBER IN ANY PURPORTED CLASS ACTION LAWSUIT." key="terms_dispute_waiver"}}</p>
            <p><strong>{{t "Informal Resolution:" key="terms_dispute_informal_heading"}}</strong> {{t "Before filing a formal legal claim, you agree to attempt to resolve the dispute informally by contacting us at legal@lingolinq.com. If the dispute is not resolved within 30 days of submission, either party may bring a formal proceeding." key="terms_dispute_informal"}}</p>
            <p><strong>{{t "Public Institution Exception:" key="terms_dispute_public_heading"}}</strong> {{t "If you are a public educational institution, state agency, or federal government entity utilizing LingoLinq in your official capacity, and you are legally prohibited from agreeing to the governing law or venue clauses above, this Choice of Law and Venue clause will not apply to you. Instead, this Agreement will be governed by the applicable laws of your jurisdiction, and venue shall be established as required by your local statutes." key="terms_dispute_public"}}</p>

